        About this item

        • FROM CAR SEAT TO STROLLER IN SECONDS - Whether you’re running errands or traveling by car, train, or plane, Doona is the complete travel system. Move from car seat to stroller at the click of a button, without disturbing your sleeping child.
        • EASY TO USE - With an adjustable handlebar, washable materials, and an intuitive design, Doona’s one-click, secure mechanism ensures correct installation every time—and allows you to explore the world with an infant, with freedom and flexibility.
        • ERGONOMIC SUPPORT - Doona is designed to ensure your baby’s body is properly supported. The Doona Infant Insert’s near-flat ergonomic design boosts your newborn’s upper and lower back and ensures the neck & back are aligned.
        • SAFE - Includes 3-layer side impact protection, anti-rebound bar crash technology & a 5-point safety harness. It’s TUV and FAA aircraft approved for travel, made with baby-safe materials & the canopy is water repellant with UPF 50+ sun protection.
        • MADE TO LAST - Doona is made from premium-grade fiber-reinforced polymers, rust-free aluminum, and durable wheels. It’s the only car seat to have been tested and certified as a rear-facing car seat, a stroller, and an infant carrier.
        • WHAT’S INCLUDED - The Doona Car Seat & Stroller includes the Doona Car Seat, the Doona Stroller, the Doona Infant Insert and Head Support, the Doona Vehicle Seat Protector, and the Doona LATCH Car Seat Base.
        • SPECS - Suitable from 4 lbs. to 35 lbs., max. 32 in height. Rear-facing car seat only. Car seat weighs 16.5 lbs., base weighs 10.3 lbs. Product Dimensions: Folded: 27.95 x 18.31 x 19.88 inches; Unfolded: 39 x 17.3 x 32.2 inches; Weight: 16.5 lbs.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Watching a tutorial on YouTube made it much easier.Pros:-We literally have taken it everywhere!! When it’s warm we go on multiple walks a day and it has held up perfectly.-It maneuvers so well that I can push the Doona around one handed even while turning.-When we go out to eat it fits next to the table so we can see her and not have to have her in a car seat on the ground.-It’s nice to bring the Doona to church!         5.0 out of 5 stars Life changing
        Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2024
        Color: Nitro BlackVerified Purchase
        This is a life changing product for newborns- the number of previous parents who have stopped us to complain that nothing like that existed for them is comical. It’s so easy to maneuver, the adjustable handle makes it easy and fun for siblings to push. It is extremely lightweight as a stroller, however, gets pretty heavy to hold as a car seat as the baby gets bigger. This can usually be mitigated by dropping the wheels and pushing it whenever possible.
        Only downside is that there is no cup holder/storage. You can buy the attachments but they’re a pain as they have to come off when you put the seat into the car base.         5.0 out of 5 stars Did I ever think a car seat would make me happy?
        Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        The answer is no but it sure does make life simpler. I looked up car seats forever. I was nervous about our first baby so I wanted to get a great car seat. The whole car seat and baby stroller industry is a joke. Generally not many products are made to adapt to a growing baby. If you find a great stroller then the baby seat does not adjust from infant to baby to child. If anything comes close you are generally paying for it. Then lets get into car seat bases, dear lord lets say we did and don't. Anyways here is my review.

        Pros
        1 - The base is a breeze to use. Simply locks the seat into place and releases easily.
        2 - The ability to strap the seat without a base. It is easy to do as also.
        3 - It turns into a freaking stroller. It does so with ease.
        4 - Safety. The handle adjusts to help with impacts to secure the car seat.
        5 - Maneuverability. This stroller turns on a dime, very fluent.
        6 - Ability to travel on a plane.

        Pros/Cons
        1 - If you are tall (well over 6') you might not enjoy the handle on the stroller. If you are smaller or a medium person by height this is perfect.
        2 - Comfort. My infant finds it to be very comfortable, then again we did add more padding.

        Cons
        1 - Price. Yep the price.
        2 - When releasing the button to turn the seat into a stroller jars a bit. So I made sure to set the car seat down first then turn it into a stroller.
        3 - Lack on storage. You have to buy accessories to clip onto the stroller from the company.
        4 - Weight. It is not light but from what other parents have told me that most car seats never feel light and are a pain to lug around. For me I have no problem. My wife finds it to be heavy.

        Overall I love this car seat stroller freak of nature. I could not imagine not using this, every car seat should have this function. If one finds it too heavy simple stop lugging the car seat around and turn it into a stroller. It's built well and meant to be a little abused. I also like the peace of mind that it was certified by the US and EU standards, it has passed many tests as it states on the part stickers all over the Doona. I find it funny how I hesitated to purchase this. If I came to the same situation again I would buy this hands down again and again.
